times.com%2Findia%2Fsupreme-court-rejects-arvind-kejriwals-plea-for-7-day-extension-of-interim-bail-will-have-to-surrender-on-june-2%2Farticleshow%2F110523054.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fsupreme-court-rejects-arvind-kejriwals-plea-for-7-day-extension-of-interim-bail-will-have-to-surrender-on-june-2%2Farticleshow%2F110523054.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Starless%2C%20Forever%20Alone%3A%207%20More%20Rogue%20Planets%20Discovered%20By%20Euclid%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Euclid%20space%20telescope%20has%20discovered%20seven%20more%20rogue%20planets%2C%20shining%20a%20light%20on%20the%20dark%20and%20lonely%20worlds%20floating%20freely%20through%20the%20universe%20untethered%20to%20any%20star.%20Without%20being%20bound%20to%20a%20star%2C%20as%20the%20Earth%20is%20to%20the%20Sun%2C%20there%20are%20no%20days%20or%20years%20on%20these%20planets%2C%20which%20languish%20in%20perpetual%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20scientists%20believe%20there%20is%20a%20chance%20they%20could%20be%20able%20to%20host%20life%20--%20and%20estimate%20there%20may%20be%20trillions%20dotted%20throughout%20the%20Milky%20Way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%20the%20European%20Space%20Agency%20released%20the%20Euclid%20telescope's%20first%20scientific%20results%20since%20the%20mission%20launched%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20discoveries%20were%20seven%20new%20free-floating%20planets%2C%20gas%20giants%20at%20least%20four%20times%20the%20mass%20of%20Jupiter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20spotted%20in%20the%20Orion%20Nebula%2C%20the%20nearest%20star-forming%20region%20to%20Earth%2C%20roughly%201%2C500%20light%20years%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEuclid%20also%20confirmed%20the%20existence%20of%20dozens%20of%20other%20previously%20detected%20rogue%20planets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpanish%20astronomer%20Eduardo%20Martin%2C%20the%20lead%20author%20of%20a%20pre-print%20study%20published%20on%20arXiv.org%20Friday%2C%20said%20this%20was%20likely%20just%20the%20%26quot%3Btip%20of%20the%20iceberg%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBecause%20they%20do%20not%20reflect%20the%20light%20of%20a%20star%2C%20spotting%20rogue%20planets%20is%20like%20%26quot%3Bfinding%20a%20needle%20in%20a%20haystack%26quot%3B%2C%20Martin%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYounger%20planets%2C%20such%20as%20those%20discovered%20by%20Euclid%2C%20are%20hotter%2C%20making%20them%20a%20little%20easier%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Awe%20and%20mystery'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20research%20has%20suggested%20there%20are%20around%2020%20rogue%20planets%20for%20every%20star%2C%20which%20could%20put%20their%20number%20in%20the%20trillions%20in%20our%20home%20galaxy%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20there%20are%20thought%20to%20be%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20galaxies%20across%20the%20universe%2C%20the%20potential%20number%20of%20free-floating%20worlds%20becomes%20difficult%20to%20fathom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20NASA's%20Roman%20space%20telescope%20launches%20in%202027%20it%20is%20expected%20find%20many%20more%20rogue%20planets%2C%20possibly%20offering%20clarity%20about%20how%20many%20could%20be%20out%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGavin%20Coleman%2C%20an%20astronomer%20at%20the%20Queen%20Mary%20University%20of%20London%20who%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20Euclid%20research%2C%20said%20these%20strange%20worlds%20often%20evoked%20%26quot%3Bfeelings%20of%20awe%20and%20mystery%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20all%20grown%20up%20with%20the%20Sun%20in%20the%20sky%2C%20and%20so%20to%20think%20of%20a%20planet%20just%20drifting%20throughout%20space%20with%20no%20star%20on%20their%20horizon%20is%20fascinating%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20not%20all%20rogue%20planets%20wander%20alone.%20Four%20of%20the%20more%20than%2020%20confirmed%20by%20Euclid%20are%20believed%20to%20be%20binaries%20--%20two%20planets%20orbiting%20each%20other%20in%20a%20single%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ECould%20they%20host%20life%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20rogue%20planets%20are%20habitable%2C%20they%20could%20be%20a%20key%20target%20in%20humanity's%20search%20for%20extraterrestrial%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20of%20our%20closest%20neighbours%20are%20likely%20rogue%20planets%2C%26quot%3B%20Martin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELacking%20heat%20from%20a%20nearby%20star%2C%20free-floating%20planets%20are%20believed%20to%20be%20cold%2C%20with%20frozen%20surfaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20any%20life-supporting%20energy%20would%20have%20to%20come%20from%20inside%20the%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20Neptune's%20energy%20comes%20from%20within%2C%20Coleman%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20geothermal%20vents%20allow%20animals%20to%20survive%20on%20Earth%20that%20have%20never%20seen%20the%20Sun's%20rays.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20under%20the%20best%20conditions%2C%20this%20extreme%20isolation%20would%20likely%20be%20able%20to%20support%20only%20bacterial%20and%20microbial%20life%2C%20Coleman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdvantage%20of%20being%20alone%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERogue%20planets%20could%20be%20thought%20of%20as%20traversing%20a%20lonely%20path%20through%20the%20cosmos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20%26quot%3Bbeing%20around%20a%20star%20has%20its%20downsides%26quot%3B%2C%20said%20study%20co-author%20Christopher%20Conselice%2C%20professor%20of%20extragalactic%20astronomy%20at%20the%20UK's%20University%20of%20Manchester.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20particular%20downside%20comes%20to%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20Sun%20becomes%20a%20red%20giant%20--%20in%20an%20estimated%207.6%20billion%20years%20--%20it%20will%20greatly%20expand%2C%20swallowing%20the%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERogue%20planets%20do%20not%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20eventually%20being%20destroyed%20by%20a%20star.%20%26quot%3BThese%20things%20will%20last%20forever%2C%26quot%3B%20Conselice%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20mind%20the%20cold%20temperatures%20you%20could%20survive%20on%20these%20planets%20for%20eternity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Euclid%20study%20also%20offered%20clues%20to%20how%20rogue%20planets%20are%20created%2C%20Conselice%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20could%20be%20formed%20in%20the%20outer%20part%20of%20a%20solar%20system%20before%20getting%20detached%20from%20their%20star%20and%20floating%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20study%20indicates%20that%20many%20rogue%20planets%20may%20be%20created%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bnatural%20byproduct%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20star-formation%20process%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20suggests%20a%20%26quot%3Breally%20close%20connection%20between%20stars%20and%20planets%20and%20how%20they%20form%26quot%3B%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20firm%20answers%20yet%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716960360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2F0r6t6f1o_euclid-rogue-planets-_625x300_29_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fstarless-forever-alone-7-more-rogue-planets-discovered-by-euclid-telescope-5769350%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Euclid%20space%20telescope%20has%20discovered%20seven%20more%20rogue%20planets%2C%20shining%20a%20light%20on%20the%20dark%20and%20lonely%20worlds%20floating%20freely%20through%20the%20universe%20untethered%20to%20any%20star.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fstarless-forever-alon