for%20'The%20Godfather'%20and%20subsequent%20collaboration%20with%20Clint%20Eastwood%20in%20'Million%20Dollar%20Baby'%20remain%20highlights%20of%20his%20illustrious%20career.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fhollywood%2Fnews%2Falbert-s-ruddy-producer-of-the-godfather-passes-away-at-94%2Farticleshow%2F110517775.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Charred%20Bodies%2C%20Children%20Screaming%3A%20Rafah%20Refugee%20Camp%20Recounts%20Horror%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Rafah%20refugee%20camp%20in%20Gaza%20witnessed%20scenes%20of%20horror%20and%20devastation%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20an%20Israeli%20airstrike%20on%20Sunday.%20Tents%20were%20engulfed%20in%20flames%2C%20and%20the%20cries%20of%20burn%20victims%20filled%20the%20air%20after%20the%20attack%2C%20which%20the%20Gaza%20Health%20Ministry%20attributed%20to%20Israeli%20forces%20targeting%20displaced%20Palestinians%20seeking%20refuge%20in%20camps.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGaza's%20civil%20defence%20agency%20reported%20that%20the%20death%20count%20had%20risen%20to%2045%20from%20the%20overnight%20strikes%2C%20which%20ignited%20tents%20and%20sparked%20widespread%20condemnation%20across%20the%20globe.%20The%20agency%20described%20the%20aftermath%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bmassacre%2C%26quot%3B%20with%20many%20bodies%20charred%20beyond%20recognition%20and%20numerous%20victims%20suffering%20severe%20injuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20saw%20charred%20bodies%20and%20dismembered%20limbs%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mohammad%20al-Mughayyir%2C%20an%20official%20from%20the%20civil%20defence%20agency%2C%20as%20quoted%20by%20news%20agency%20AFP.%20%26quot%3BWe%20also%20saw%20cases%20of%20amputations%2C%20wounded%20children%2C%20women%2C%20and%20the%20elderly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFootage%20captured%20by%20the%20Palestinian%20Red%20Crescent%20Society%20showed%20chaotic%20scenes%20as%20paramedics%20worked%20tirelessly%20to%20evacuate%20the%20wounded%2C%20including%20many%20children.%20The%20night%20was%20filled%20with%20the%20sounds%20of%20sirens%20and%20the%20anguished%20cries%20of%20survivors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20just%20finished%20evening%20prayers%2C%26quot%3B%20recalled%20one%20survivor.%20%26quot%3BOur%20children%20were%20asleep%20when%20we%20heard%20a%20loud%20sound%2C%20and%20suddenly%20there%20was%20fire%20all%20around%20us.%20The%20children%20were%20screaming...%20the%20sound%20was%20terrifying.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Israeli%20army%20claimed%20that%20their%20aircraft%20had%20targeted%20a%20Hamas%20compound%20in%20Rafah%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20deaths%20of%20two%20senior%20Hamas%20operatives%2C%20Yassin%20Rabia%20and%20Khaled%20Nagar.%20They%20acknowledged%20reports%20of%20civilian%20casualties%20due%20to%20the%20strike%20and%20the%20subsequent%20fire%2C%20stating%20that%20the%20incident%20was%20under%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20airstrike%20provoked%20strong%20reactions%20from%20neighbouring%20Arab%20nations.%20Egypt%2C%20Jordan%2C%20Kuwait%2C%20and%20Qatar%20condemned%20the%20attack%2C%20with%20Qatar%20warning%20that%20it%20could%20hinder%20ongoing%20efforts%20to%20revive%20truce%20and%20hostage%20release%20talks%20in%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20conflict%2C%20which%20has%20been%20ongoing%20since%20October%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20Nations%20Relief%20and%20Works%20Agency%20for%20Palestine%20Refugees%20(UNRWA)%20described%20the%20attack%20as%20%26quot%3Bhorrifying%26quot%3B%20and%20shared%20on%20social%20media%20that%20the%20images%20from%20the%20site%20were%20%26quot%3Byet%20another%20testament%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20dire%20conditions%20in%20Gaza.%20Multiple%20videos%20showed%20fires%20raging%20through%20the%20camp%20and%20people%20desperately%20pulling%20bodies%20from%20the%20rubble.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20morning%2C%20the%20charred%20remains%20of%20tents%20and%20vehicles%20were%20all%20that%20was%20left%20of%20the%20refugee%20camp%20in%20Rafah%20known%20as%20the%20Kuwaiti%20Al-Salam%20Camp%201.%20An%20aid%20group%2C%20Al-Salam%20Association%20for%20Humanitarian%20and%20Charitable%20Works%2C%20reported%20that%20besides%20the%20dozens%20of%20deaths%20and%20injuries%2C%20over%20120%20tents%20and%20several%20facilities%20were%20destroyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBilal%20al-Sapti%2C%20a%2030-year-old%20construction%20worker%20from%20Rafah%2C%20recounted%20the%20devastation%20he%20witnessed.%20%26quot%3BThe%20fire%20was%20very%20strong%20and%20was%20all%20over%20the%20camp%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20darkness%20and%20no%20electricity.%26quot%3B%20Despite%20the%20destruction%2C%20his%20family%20miraculously%20survived.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20of%20the%20dead%20bodies%20were%20severely%20burned%2C%20had%20amputated%20limbs%20and%20were%20torn%20to%20pieces%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Flive%2F2024%2F05%2F27%2Fworld%2Fisrael-gaza-war-hamas-rafah%3FsearchResultPosition%3D3%23charred-bodies-and-screams-witnesses-describe-scenes-of-horror-at-a-camp%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20Dr%20Marwan%20al-Hams%2C%20a%20healthcare%20worker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UN%20reported%20that%20one%20million%20civilians%20had%20fled%20Rafah%20since%20the%20start%20of%20Israel's%20assault%20in%20early%20May%2C%20despite%20numerous%20international%20warnings%20against%20the%20escalating%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conflict%2C%20the%20deadliest%20in%20Gaza's%20history%2C%20began%20with%20a%20deadly%20attack%20by%20Hamas%20on%20southern%20Israel%20on%20October%207%2C%20resulting%20in%201%2C189%20Israeli%20deaths%20and%20252%20hostages%20taken.%20Israel's%20response%20has%20been%20relentless%2C%20with%20the%20Gaza%20Health%20Ministry%20reporting%20over%2036%2C096%20deaths%2C%20mostly%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716951300000%2C%22vi