made-by-award-winning-kashmir-organic-farmer-anantnag-units-earns-crores%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20to%20compost%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20among%20other%20activities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%20this%20work%20along%20with%20his%20job%20in%20different%20companies%20including%20Shell%2C%20IBM%2C%20Accenture%2C%20British%20Petroleum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202019%20water%20crisis%20and%20his%20bad%20experience%20made%20him%20start%20looking%20for%20sustainable%20solutions.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20also%20realised%20that%20corporate%20life%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20for%20him%20anymore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWorking%20for%20a%20paycheck%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20cutting%20it%20for%20me%20anymore.%20When%20you%20reach%20a%20certain%20level%20of%20financial%20security%2C%20you%20should%20consider%20giving%20back%20to%20society%2C%20and%20for%20me%2C%20that%20was%20greywater%20recycling%2C%E2%80%9D%20Prashant%20shares.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20shares%20that%20climate%20change%20has%20reached%20a%20stage%20where%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20can%20now%20no%20longer%20afford%20to%20be%20a%20passive%20spectator%20to%20the%20carnage%20being%20done%20to%20our%20environment.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWater%20is%20obviously%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20problems%20in%20the%20world%20today.%20I%20saw%20firsthand%20in%20Chennai%20how%20desperate%20people%20can%20become%20when%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20water.%20I%20also%20visited%20a%20lot%20of%20villages%20after%202019%20and%20looked%20at%20ways%20I%20could%20contribute.%20I%20found%20my%20calling%20in%20water%20conservation%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Prashant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20research%2C%20he%20found%20that%20greywater%20was%20something%20that%20could%20be%20recycled.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20100%20litres%20of%20water%20are%20being%20released%2C%20almost%2070%20litres%20of%20that%20is%20greywater%2C%20i.e.%20non-faecal%20water%20with%20minimum%20impurities%2C%20which%20can%20be%20easily%20recycled.%20Urban%20India%20generates%20about%2070%20litres%20of%20greywater%20per%20person%20per%20day%2C%20but%20in%20almost%20100%20percent%20cases%2C%20this%20greywater%20is%20simply%20mixed%20with%20sewage%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsually%20what%20happens%20is%20that%20this%20greywater%20gets%20mixed%20with%20the%20sewage%20water%20and%20is%20sent%20to%20Sewage%20Treatment%20Plants%20(STP)%20or%20just%20discharged%20openly%2C%20impacting%20livelihoods%2C%20crop%20productivity%20and%20an%20increase%20in%20vector%20borne%20diseases%2C%20explains%20Prashant.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%20that%20STPs%20are%20one%20of%20the%20most%20polluting%20industries%2C%20%E2%80%9Cconsuming%20about%20three%20percent%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20energy.%E2%80%9D%20Therefore%2C%20recycling%20greywater%20near%20its%20source%20is%20sustainable%20and%20a%20possible%20solution%20to%20solve%20the%20global%20water%20crisis.%20The%20DownToEarth%20report%20also%20states%20that%20%E2%80%9Creuse%20of%20greywater%20for%20toilet%20flushing%20alone%20can%20reduce%20the%20freshwater%20demand%20by%2010-20%20percent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGreywater%20recycling%20is%20also%20very%20simple%2C%20starting%20with%20using%20cooking%20water%20to%20water%20plants%2C%20and%20for%20flushing.%20It%20also%20requires%20no%20electricity%20or%20chemicals.%20It%20treats%20the%20waste%20water%20at%20source%2C%20making%20it%20a%20decentralised%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20idea%20was%20set%2C%20Prashant%20worked%20on%20a%20nature-based%20solution%20to%20recycle%20greywater-%20Constructed%20Wetlands%20(CW)%2C%20which%20are%20built%20using%20natural%20filter%20materials%20like%20activated%20charcoal%2C%20stone%2C%20grit%2C%20sand.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConstructed%20wetlands%20are%20man-made%20wastewater%20recycling%20systems%20which%20resemble%20natural%20wetlands%20in%20treatment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-